	 ('Third-World-Skeptical-Kid','This meme template features a close-up image of two individuals in what appears to be a rural or village setting. The focal point is a young African boy, likely around 4-6 years old, wearing a striped polo shirt in light yellow and gray. He has a distinctive expression on his face - a mixture of skepticism, mild annoyance, and perhaps a touch of sass. His eyes are slightly narrowed and his mouth is set in a subtle, knowing smirk.

To the left of the boy is a portion of another person''s face and upper body. This individual appears to be a woman with long dark hair, leaning towards the boy as if in conversation. Only part of her face is visible, but her posture suggests she''s engaging with or speaking to the boy.

The background hints at a rustic environment. There''s what looks like a bamboo or reed fence or wall behind them, and the ground appears to be bare earth, suggesting an outdoor setting in a less developed area.

This image has become a popular meme template due to the boy''s expressive face, which often conveys a sense of doubt, skepticism, or a "you can''t fool me" attitude. It''s frequently used to express disbelief or suspicion about someone''s claims or statements, playing on the boy''s seemingly worldly-wise expression despite his young age.

The contrast between the boy''s confident, almost adult-like expression and his young age adds to the humor and versatility of the meme. It can be used to comment on a wide range of situations where someone is unconvinced or sees through an obvious lie or exaggeration.','/memes/Third-World-Skeptical-Kid.jpg',2,'{}','{"African skeptical child","so your telling me","so you''re telling me","skeptical african kid",full,"so your telling me......","african boy","\"so you mean to tell me\" meme template"}',0.0,'[0.037350345,-0.001228923,-0.004277165,0.022064127,0.016421074,-0.03253099,-0.011047511,-0.00021986819,-0.005173147,0.031080684,0.015060857,-0.013393831,0.02355623,0.02321999,-0.017895002,-0.009820383,-0.0038925072,-0.02264639,-0.003072027,0.008534914,0.014571669,0.00821241,-0.07767584,-0.034056462,-0.0011532654,0.057074107,-0.004849663,0.012565237,0.041010953,0.043946087,0.0023074204,0.026102336,0.0029063069,-0.026341148,-0.01615294,-0.012089621,0.05242162,-0.032301154,-0.039855927,-0.034195058,0.025408495,-7.034973e-05,0.025750453,-0.0027060618,-0.034950115,-0.020395884,-0.014257316,-0.017287122,0.027557861,0.032725956,0.025326068,-0.010312526,0.028041469,-0.0021383364,-0.056027513,-0.041954003,-0.004162216,-0.015009967,0.0063776225,0.01734132,0.038007334,0.025097962,-0.002181161,-0.055981558,-0.029844295,0.0035194464,-0.02040512,-0.006231622,-0.025047166,-0.009165099,0.006506931,0.012692754,-0.00963507,-0.022235814,-0.030254941,-0.00062051776,-0.026802674,0.0014393531,0.02712994,0.022130232,0.05362922,0.035288293,0.00825798,-0.037072558,-0.017719612,-0.014207331,0.030041412,0.029422235,-0.009311159,-0.007645748,0.0071053756,0.043949917,-0.031046206,-0.017521916,0.05270176,0.054961964,-0.013460154,0.03016686,-0.0043997206,-0.005187678,-0.013088178,0.043063026,-0.016772186,0.031809457,-0.02929548,0.005324437,0.011713919,-0.03440268,-0.06703783,-0.003134647,0.011525009,-0.033422336,0.012762662,-0.019322118,-0.021299805,0.04331352,0.00013253995,0.03769319,-0.03455555