	 ('Bad-Luck-Brian','This meme template features a portrait-style photograph of a young man, likely a teenager, set against a dark purple background typical of school portraits from the 1990s or early 2000s. The subject has a distinctive appearance that has made this image iconic in meme culture.

The young man is wearing a red plaid sweater vest over a light blue collared shirt, creating a preppy or nerdy aesthetic common in that era. His hair is short and neatly combed, with a slight reddish tint that complements the red in his vest.

What makes this image particularly memorable is the subject''s facial expression. He has an extremely wide, somewhat awkward smile that reveals braces on his teeth. His eyes are slightly squinted due to the breadth of his grin, giving him an exaggerated look of enthusiasm or forced happiness.

The lighting in the photograph casts a slight sheen on the subject''s face, emphasizing his features and adding to the somewhat uncomfortable quality of the image. The combination of the dated style, the exaggerated expression, and the general awkwardness of the pose has made this image a popular template for memes often used to express situations of social discomfort, forced positivity, or ironic enthusiasm.

The image is tightly cropped around the subject''s head and shoulders, focusing all attention on his face and expression. This close framing amplifies the impact of the smile and contributes to the image''s effectiveness as a reaction meme or representational image for various socially awkward scenarios.

This template has become deeply ingrained in internet culture, often used to convey feelings of discomfort, social anxiety, or attempts to appear normal in abnormal situations. Its enduring popularity speaks to its versatility in expressing a wide range of relatable, often self-deprecating sentiments.','/memes/Bad-Luck-Brian.jpg',2,'{}','{"bad luck brian nerdy","bad luck brian cry","unlucky ginger kid","loser boy"}',0.0,'[0.029924799,-0.04149817,0.026786705,0.02624986,0.008024513,-0.053812396,-0.01017123,-0.026049716,-0.014826991,0.029124742,-0.0010286969,-0.049625445,0.044453967,0.0028852513,-0.004255149,-0.011000572,-0.004129297,-0.04360324,-0.0432965,0.038741753,0.0046795798,-0.0104476875,-0.059153322,-0.031877805,-0.0015580241,0.033805322,-0.006375326,0.010119705,0.04248517,0.009140038,0.00731957,0.006848781,-0.024124382,-0.035338473,0.006359868,0.008889859,0.027938424,-0.055844214,-0.0049914974,-0.00705933,0.029062113,-0.016670771,0.015342798,-0.0074477857,-0.0010505525,-0.018797664,0.0049944785,-0.018849527,0.045026477,0.00064291595,-0.0058617173,-0.034992363,0.009601561,0.04452162,-0.007294312,-0.03374729,0.0033127111,0.0027763927,0.023722166,0.030511206,0.02919893,0.036754794,0.00019625461,-0.034212247,-0.027000261,-0.0013618944,0.004013873,0.000732668,-0.012597307,-0.009213775,-0.002253761,-0.016590012,-0.0044265427,0.022186257,-0.034118462,-0.015479901,-0.040095016,-0.029449802,0.038447745,0.011203194,0.043970026,0.030264532,0.0044353344,-0.028915314,-0.029636204,-0.0046718693,0.003652779,0.036372297,-0.0056549096,-0.03150908,-0.019143308,0.051561855,-0.0134136025,0.0065329494,0.0073824255,0.03502676,0.019455357,0.0422454,0.0026103524,0.016041284,0.007525452,0.053147104,-0.031577535,0.053771235,-0.03006991,0.0100008575,0.03191902,-0.03363467,-0.047928225,-0.030603694,-0.003113109,-0.03601631,-0.011908924,-0.009348101,-0.036546756,0.028982705,0.00041084285,0.046615362,-0.02744902,-0.022341518,-0.050607335,0.004971581,-0.005354228,-0.03154431,-0.018631378,-0