	 ('Who-Would-Win','This meme template is a minimalist and versatile image designed for comparative humor. The template consists of a stark white background with bold black text and simple black lines creating a basic structure.

At the top of the image, centered and in large, capitalized letters, is the phrase "WHO WOULD WIN?" This text serves as the setup for the meme, prompting the viewer to consider a hypothetical contest or comparison between two entities.

Below this text, the image is divided into two equal sections by a vertical black line that extends from just below the text to the bottom of the image. This line creates two distinct spaces on either side, each intended to contain an image, text, or both, representing the two subjects being compared.

A horizontal black line runs across the top of these sections, separating them from the introductory text. This creates a clean, table-like structure that clearly delineates the competing elements.

The simplicity of this template allows for great flexibility in its use. Meme creators can insert images, text, or a combination of both into the two sections to create humorous, often absurd comparisons. The stark contrast and clean lines make it easy to read and understand quickly, which is crucial for meme effectiveness.

This format taps into the internet culture''s love for versus-style debates and unexpected juxtapositions. It can be used to compare anything from pop culture references to historical events, or even abstract concepts, often with a comedic twist that subverts expectations.

The "Who Would Win?" template has become a staple in meme culture, recognized widely for its simple yet effective format that encourages creativity and often results in viral content across various social media platforms.','/memes/Who-Would-Win.jpg',2,'{}','{}',0.0,'[0.008612141,-0.033327356,0.018042523,-0.01411693,-0.009071911,-0.047934134,-0.066050135,-0.007508159,-0.011721815,0.04420817,-0.0027448793,0.016792644,0.03785197,-0.0064027966,-0.0071115536,-0.018171072,-0.02220793,-0.03418647,-0.02283883,-0.014201331,-0.01394746,0.016538441,-0.07541353,-0.030803123,0.009855742,0.03482997,0.007985704,0.031124199,0.069836594,0.017779093,0.012258443,-0.01984431,-0.004892609,-0.053576373,-0.016331112,-0.015102285,0.0345634,-0.046290405,-0.049074266,-0.011448472,0.029434888,-0.03336167,0.028798062,-0.0032455162,-0.051483598,-0.019460492,-0.02035806,0.0014017483,-0.0025710938,-0.032149807,-0.015981775,-0.025757948,0.03205697,-0.01680725,-0.035796814,-0.004814901,-0.026603196,-0.015869997,-0.018806528,0.069501534,0.048027307,0.0125382785,0.017153436,-0.056844752,-0.00443202,-0.022811288,0.031655908,-0.032196175,-0.013774455,-0.009876307,-0.011140264,-0.0069698873,-0.015270945,-0.02042463,-0.036766175,-0.012354786,-0.019039951,-0.046361078,0.007253682,0.025763066,0.023479262,0.08100594,0.0045193466,-0.035918843,-0.03811178,-0.022400733,0.042878043,0.004779604,0.035589024,-0.02618229,-0.018124135,0.04941079,0.01346128,0.012921635,0.019567728,0.024999721,-0.0081030885,0.032682985,5.4147673e-05,0.011636556,0.026135726,0.043939374,-0.022033077,0.050288577,-0.04311572,0.020378392,0.01508924,-0.01882458,-0.05715443,-0.03418529,0.0012271174,-0.008423537,0.008143791,-0.0071711466,-0.01626779,0.017564049,0.00984669,0.07356837,-0.0531189,0.010764159,-0.058791693,0.0066367425,-0.050473463,0.0063111917,-0.031580016,-0.0076557607,0.0026788756,0.027217925,-0.027960246,-0.010146745,0.028210089,-0.031492963,0.0115400925,0.04204118,-0.037298735,0.06808474,0.018159978,0.030078586,0.040661324,-0