	 ('Ill-Just-Wait-Here','This meme template consists of two vertically stacked images, both depicting a character sitting in front of a computer monitor in a darkened setting.

In the top panel, we see a middle-aged man with a stern, intense expression. His face is illuminated from the side, likely by the glow of the computer screen, creating dramatic shadows that emphasize his furrowed brow and tense jaw. He''s wearing a light-colored suit jacket and tie, suggesting a professional or business setting. The man appears to be concentrating deeply on whatever is displayed on the monitor in front of him.

The bottom panel presents a shocking transformation. In place of the man, we now see a grotesque, zombie-like creature in the same position. This figure has pale, mottled skin stretched tightly over a skull-like face with sunken eyes and exposed teeth in a grimace. Long, stringy white hair hangs from its head. The creature is still wearing the suit and tie, creating a jarring contrast between its monstrous appearance and the professional attire.

This template is often used to humorously depict the transformative (and often negative) effects of prolonged computer use or exposure to disturbing online content. The dramatic shift from a normal human to a ghoulish creature emphasizes the idea of a profound and unsettling change occurring while engaging with digital media.

The dark background and the eerie lighting contribute to a mood of suspense and horror, amplifying the impact of the transformation. The computer monitor, visible in both frames, serves as a constant element linking the before and after states, implying it''s the source or catalyst of the change.

This meme format is particularly effective for commenting on internet culture, the addictive nature of technology, or reactions to shocking or time-consuming online experiences.','/memes/Ill-Just-Wait-Here.jpg',2,'{}','{"waiting skeleton","still waiting",skull,"i''ll just wait here guy","skeleton waiting","skeleton still waiting","waiting indiana jones"}',0.0,'[0.024628015,-0.052548546,0.015188266,0.026028348,0.0293381,-0.06588931,-0.017854858,-0.010200755,-0.019277511,0.041470878,0.014667971,-0.03709694,0.0349189,0.00044201638,0.006109469,-0.0047332346,-0.004500486,-0.028917981,-0.041935757,0.018339466,0.017000865,0.008345281,-0.055996295,-0.047552124,-0.032650303,0.06484034,-0.003917284,0.008173404,0.046885677,0.023359023,0.0028875459,-0.006199832,-0.012138716,-0.042764153,-0.0023225294,0.008664827,0.028885657,-0.07816055,-0.019497858,-0.031506,0.040791176,-0.020322144,0.022262072,-0.032656025,-0.03162837,-0.015103282,0.005118204,-0.016668955,0.016862841,-0.012076781,0.018933212,-0.017310364,0.002219234,0.027781717,-0.010875394,-0.054297008,-0.004724486,-0.009820482,-0.0011688028,0.016306842,0.053656787,0.020106515,0.01142961,-0.049852498,-0.02005945,0.01900653,-0.010092802,-0.0050828196,-0.024319006,0.033344,-0.013601847,0.021555202,0.014658446,0.018419225,-0.02311657,-0.00340732,-0.04267948,-0.043520488,0.009356504,0.011934299,-0.010643951,0.02959141,0.005547443,-0.01291955,-0.022115856,-0.029479958,0.01670424,0.033326685,0.018454026,-0.0053723496,0.018224452,0.027734423,0.013810387,0.0056874924,-0.0043695476,0.06586303,-0.010452305,0.0195653,-0.014098536,0.009462258,-0.0074916547,0.045555826,-0.03947489,0.061725758,-0.025116757,0.010200894,0.07163637,-0.0141205285,-0.059751056,-0.043948166,0.02742492,-0.026351467,-0.001277584,0.027389271,-0.040604588,0.023602445,-0.0057818512,0.04213712,-0.04504076,-0.006039128,-0.0393003,-0.03728223,-0.010378804,-0.042492624,-0.009881354,-0.024196308,0.010030137,0.04510508,-0.051911384,0.0032041767,-0.0055279094,-0.006599019,-