	 ('Two-Buttons','This meme template consists of two panels arranged vertically, creating a sequential narrative in a comic-style format.

The top panel shows a close-up view of two white rectangular panels or buttons, each containing a large red circle or button. These are presented at an angle, suggesting they''re mounted on some kind of control panel or interface. A hand enters the frame from the bottom right, with an extended index finger poised to press one of the red buttons. The background is a light blue color, giving a sense of a sterile or technological environment.

The bottom panel dramatically shifts focus to show the consequences of the button press. It depicts a man''s face and upper body in a state of extreme stress or panic. The man has short brown hair and is wearing a red shirt. His facial expression is exaggerated, with wide eyes, raised eyebrows, and a grimacing mouth. Sweat droplets are prominently featured on his face, emphasizing his distress. His hand is raised to his forehead in a classic "oh no" gesture, clutching what appears to be a white cloth or handkerchief.

The art style is simplified and cartoonish, with bold lines and flat colors, typical of many internet memes and comics. The contrast between the seemingly simple act in the first panel and the exaggerated reaction in the second creates a humorous juxtaposition that''s ripe for various interpretations and captions.

This template is often used to represent difficult choices, regrettable decisions, or anxiety-inducing situations where any option leads to stress or negative outcomes. The exaggerated reaction in the second panel lends itself to humorous exaggeration of everyday problems or more serious commentary on challenging dilemmas.

