	 ('Evil-Kermit','This meme template features a striking and enigmatic image that plays on the popular Kermit the Frog character from the Muppets, but with a dark twist. The image is split into two distinct parts, creating a compelling visual contrast.

On the left side, we see the familiar profile of Kermit the Frog. His iconic lime green, fuzzy texture is clearly visible, as are his characteristic bulbous eyes perched atop his head. Kermit appears to be looking down, giving an impression of contemplation or perhaps dejection.

On the right side, we see what appears to be another version of Kermit, but this one is shrouded in a black hooded cloak, reminiscent of a Sith lord from Star Wars or a sinister monk. Only the green of the face is visible within the darkness of the hood, creating a striking and somewhat unsettling image.

The background of the entire image is a muted, dark grey, adding to the somber and mysterious atmosphere. The lighting seems to be coming from above, casting shadows and emphasizing the textures of both Kermit figures.

This juxtaposition of the familiar, friendly Kermit with his dark, hooded counterpart creates a powerful visual metaphor. It suggests a duality, perhaps representing the internal struggle between good and evil, or the temptation to give in to one''s darker impulses. The meme format often uses this template to humorously depict moments of moral dilemma or the temptation to make questionable choices.

The image''s composition, with the two figures facing each other, adds a sense of internal dialogue or conflict, making it perfect for memes that play on the theme of being torn between two options or listening to one''s "better" or "worse" self.','/memes/Evil-Kermit.jpg',2,'{}','{"kermit me to me","kermit inner me","sith kermit","kermit dark side"}',0.0,'[0.03182141,-0.055453062,0.016824918,0.018842885,-0.008556685,-0.07908144,-0.033083085,0.008398156,-0.048414525,0.040382344,-0.009709719,-0.02210024,0.051878054,0.0060941977,-0.018145883,0.022532513,0.009242401,-0.016247502,-0.011600649,-0.020521378,-0.0031144044,0.016819172,-0.056169953,-0.006998225,0.007507434,0.057793308,0.00034749784,0.010769334,0.054918796,0.010784246,0.022611275,0.017131906,0.023074713,-0.064679295,-0.0065174787,-0.005266311,0.023798278,-0.04460001,0.011176566,-0.020002939,0.03474909,-0.020076426,0.008922399,-0.046246625,-0.017357541,-0.0015752971,-0.014539838,-0.0068833074,0.023973046,-0.020587906,-0.0047318367,-0.011802254,0.016142601,0.0062860884,-0.021376384,-0.022858702,0.008073681,-0.010493874,-0.0045654867,0.013523644,0.03648431,-0.001976679,0.011194311,-0.05561557,-0.032005526,-0.013416449,-0.023490822,-0.0025967185,-0.023220686,-0.004331588,0.0008899291,0.030628601,-0.0044365046,0.0067530065,-0.02486897,-0.014247296,-0.03292215,-0.0149339335,0.02386271,0.011265557,0.019471329,0.015131867,-0.024774104,-0.013255339,-0.012617612,-0.009717626,-0.010614725,0.03068878,0.021851266,-0.016807958,-0.0051432922,0.07909036,0.00028665445,0.015065055,0.014829493,0.039653663,0.0066067176,0.016571805,-0.020840969,0.0033838977,-0.0070244125,0.024109133,-0.026331874,0.049469516,-0.035375487,-0.02583854,0.026664251,0.007983856,-0.03661525,-0.019985963,0.022665216,-0.029651634,0.017796814,0.00032802013,-0.031748928,0.0140664885,-0.01483718,0.044960026,-0.05290952,-0.00702196,-0.034396943,-0.036914892,-0.036294494,0.018123044,-0.007738682,-0.008588944,-0.012163377,0.04879893,-0.041824687,0.027355835,0.01